President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key roles in his administration. N. Nick Perry is nominated for Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to Jamaica. Perry is an immigrant from Jamaica and has served for three decades as an Assemblyman in the New York State Legislature. He currently holds the position of Assistant Speaker Pro Tempore of the New York State Assembly. Kurt DelBene is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Information and Technology and Chief Information Officer at the Department of Veterans Affairs. DelBene is a technology executive and previously worked at Microsoft, where he held various senior executive positions. He also played a role in the improvement work on Healthcare.gov during the Obama-Biden administration. Mike Gerber is nominated for Member of the Federal Retirement Thrift Investment Board. Gerber is an asset management executive and has previously served in the Pennsylvania House of Representatives. He currently holds positions on various boards, including the Board of Trustees of the University of Pennsylvania.